<recipe>
<title>
Chocolate Peanut Butter Energy Bites
</title>
<details>
PREP TIME: 10 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 10 minutes
SERVINGS: 10
</details>
<ingredients>
1/2 c . unsalted almonds
2/3 c . dried pitted dates
1/4 c . bittersweet chocolate
1/4 c . natural peanut butter without sugar
2 T . unsalted peanuts
1 tsp . unsweetened cocoa powder
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Place almonds in a food processor, and pulse until finely ground.
Remove 2 tablespoons ground almonds and set aside.
Add dates, bittersweet chocolate, peanut butter, and peanuts. Pulse until finely chopped and uniformly mixed.
Scoop with medium cookie scoop (1.5 tablespoons), packing as you scoop.
Roll into a ball.
Add cocoa powder to reserved ground almonds, and stir to combine.
Roll energy bite in chocolate/almond mixture.
Enjoy immediately, or chill until ready to eat.
</instructions>
</recipe>
